to the editor re be content with small change by richard c wald op ed june 22 in 1962 our family arrived from cuba truly penniless my dad found work as a dishwasher and my mom as a housekeeper my sister and i received 13 cents every day the bus cost 5 cents each way milk at school cost 3 cents we did not lose any pennies today we are both blessed with careers but almost 40 years later i bend down pick up someone 's lost penny and give thanks gisela cardonne miami june 23 2001

